The ANC’s national executive committee has announced a proposed package of interventions to help grow the struggling economy and create jobs. The party briefed journalists at Luthuli House in Johannesburg, following a special meeting of the party’s leadership body over the weekend. Analysts say the plans will go a long way towards providing policy certainty for a clearer roadmap towards economic recovery. For now the ANC is only saying which key areas will be the focus. It is looking into a package of policy interventions that will be outlined more blatantly in the budget later this month. For more watch video below: 